Delay Check In Cytometer pane, Threshold tab Set threshold to 50% of the FCS scatter signal In Laser tab, Set the window extension to zero. Do not change timing for blue laser. Verify that the Area signals do not decrease more than 50%.when window is reduced to zero. Check the CST settings on the desktop in latest performance link to verify delay setting are correct. Check Aria Laser timing sheet posted above computer for different size nozzles If delays are off and a facility operator is not available adjust delays in half microcecond increments until maximum Area signal is found. Open window extension to 2.0 for experiment.
Area scaling Area should be = or > than the height signal within 10%. Use laser tab in Cytometer pane to make adjustmentsto Area scaling factor
